title: Elbow Grease All Purpose Degreaser, 500ml
features: The Elbow Grease All-Purpose Degreaser is perfect for removing tough grease stains from kitchen and bathroom surfaces, fabrics, carpets, plastics and even engines and machinery
The Elbow Grease All-Purpose Degreaser not only keeps the surface perfectly clean and grease-free, but it leaves a heavenly fresh lemon scent in your kitchen and bathroom that lasts for hours

UNIQUE FORMULA: This unique, solvent-free formula is gentle and safe to use for removing grease spots from delicate and coloured fabrics, yet tough enough to clean vehicle parts and metal surfaces including alloy wheels

FRESH SCENT: The Elbow Grease All-Purpose Degreaser not only keeps the surface perfectly clean and grease-free, but it leaves a heavenly fresh lemon scent in your kitchen and bathroom that lasts for hours
ABOUT THE PRODUCT: 500ml recyclable bottle. Solvent-free. Not suitable for wood. Vegan friendly
description: Product Description Remove grease and oil stains with this All-Purpose Degreaser, the miracle product from Elbow Grease. This unique, solvent-free formula is gentle and safe to use for removing grease spots from delicate and coloured fabrics, yet tough enough to clean vehicle parts and metal surfaces. Perfect for removing tough grease stains from kitchen and bathroom surfaces, carpets and more. 500ml spray bottle. Ingredients Less Than 5% Cationic Surfactants, Non-ionic Surfactants, Phosphates, Also Contains: Perfume, Limonene Safety Warning IMPORTANT: NOT SUITABLE FOR WOOD OR TRANSPARENT POLYCARBONATES SUCH AS PLASTIGLASS, PERSPEX AND VISORS - TEST BEFORE USE. DANGER: Contains: C9-11 PARETH-8, ETHANOLAMINE, QUATERNARY C12-14 ALKYL METHYLAMINE ETHOXYLATE METHYLCHLORIDE. Causes skin irritation. Causes serious eye damage. Keep out of reach of children. Read label before use. Wear eye protection. Wash hands thoroughly after handling. IF ON SKIN: Wash with plenty of soap and water. IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present and easy to do. Continue rinsing. Do not breathe mist. IF INHALED: Remove person to fresh air and keep comfortable for breathing. Immediately call a POISON CENTER/doctor. If medical advice is needed, have product container or label at hand.
